# iCUE Widget Rules

For the full build/debug workflow, use the `building-icue-widgets` skill.

## Property names become globals

Every `x-icue-property` `content` value is injected as `var <name>`. Never declare a JS identifier with the same name.

```javascript
// BAD — pollSeconds is a property name → SyntaxError → blank widget
function pollSeconds() { ... }

// GOOD
function getPollSeconds() { return parseInt(prop("pollSeconds"), 10) || 60; }
function prop(name) { return window[name] || DEFAULTS[name]; }
```

## Strict HTML (iCUE importer > CLI validator)

- `<!DOCTYPE html>` uppercase
- No self-closing void tags: `<meta ...>` not `<meta ... />`
- Real `<title>` and viewport meta required

## Lifecycle

- `start()` must be idempotent and run on `DOMContentLoaded`
- Do not gate rendering on `iCUE_initialized` or wait for `onICUEInitialized`

## Sizing

- Use `rem` + JS `fitFont()` with `ResizeObserver`; avoid `vh`/`vw` clamps on Xeneon Edge tiles
